# Module01 🌿 — Object-Oriented Programming

## 📌 Description

Module01 focuses on Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts in Python.

The project simulates a garden system using classes and demonstrates how to design, extend, and manage objects using inheritance, encapsulation, and polymorphism.

---

## ⚙️ Features

- Class-based architecture
- Inheritance (`Plant` → `Flower`, `Tree`, `Vegetable`)
- Encapsulation (private attributes with getters/setters)
- Method overriding
- Static and class methods
- Object interaction and behavior simulation

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts

- OOP design principles
- Data encapsulation
- Code reusability via inheritance
- Polymorphism (method overriding)
- State management inside objects

---

## 📂 Structure

```
ex0 → basic introduction
ex1 → plant registry
ex2 → plant growth simulation
ex3 → factory pattern (object creation)
ex4 → data management
ex5 → validation & encapsulation
ex6 → advanced OOP (inheritance, stats, behavior)
```

---

## 💡 Example Features

- Track plant growth over time  
- Simulate plant lifecycle (grow, age, bloom)  
- Different plant types with unique behavior  
- Input validation (age, height constraints)  
- Statistics tracking for method calls  

---

